==English==
===Proverb===
'''the [[grass]] is always [[green]]er on the other side'''
#Other people's [[circumstance]]s seem more desirable than one's own.

<!--Redundant: the definition sums this point up.
Notes: Not only does this proverb use a metaphor (greenness standing for the quality of something) but it is also a statement that is evidently untrue ("other situations are always better than the status quo") that the point of it is not what it says but the fact that people tend to think so.
-->
